name: Archer Tower Mk I
description: A humble tower with a bow. It won't win any awards, but it gets the job done... sometimes.

name: Archer Tower Mk II
description: Now with sharper arrows and slightly better aim! Perfect for ruining someone's day.

name: Archer Tower Mk III
description: Advanced archery technology! Shoots faster, hits harder, and still hates flying enemies.

name: Archer Tower Mk IV
description: The pinnacle of archery engineering. It shoots arrows so fast, they might break the sound barrier!

name: Catapult Jr.
description: A basic catapult. It's not fancy, but it flings rocks like nobody's business.

name: Catapult Pro
description: Bigger rocks, longer range, and a lot more destruction. It's a rock lover's dream.

name: Catapult Supreme
description: The ultimate rock-flinging machine. If it doesn't crush your enemies, it will at least scare them.

name: Guardian Tower Mk II
description: Now with extra firepower! Literally. It burns brighter and hotter.

name: Guardian Tower Mk I
description: A fiery guardian that burns enemies and their hopes of survival. Toasty!

name: Frost Mage Tower Mk I
description: A frosty tower that slows enemies down. It's like winter came early for them.

name: Frost Mage Tower Mk II
description: Colder, meaner, and with a bigger chill factor. Enemies will freeze in their tracks.

name: Frost Mage Tower Mk III
description: The ultimate frost tower. It doesn't just slow enemies—it makes them question their life choices.

name: Vine Tower
description: A tower with a green thumb. It tangles enemies in vines and makes them regret stepping on its lawn.

name: Door Tower
description: A mysterious tower that shoots everything in sight.

name: Sprout Tower
description: A medium vine tower that shoots seeds with precision and speed. Perfect for keeping enemies at bay.

name: Seedling Tower
description: A small vine tower that pelts enemies with seeds. It's fast, but don't expect it to win any strength contests.

name: Archer Tower Mk V
description: The ultimate archer tower. Its arrows fly faster than your enemies can run, and they hit like a freight train!

name: Gamearly tower
description: Promo tower for Gamearly. It's a tower that shoots arrows. What more do you need to know?

name: Summoning systems tower
description: A tower to support the game, it's not legendary but it's still powerful and beautiful. stats : 10 damage, 120 range, 0.6 rate and 150 gold stack.

name: Bug tower
description: A free round for players who have suffered from the terrible server bug following the financial update

name: Fire eye tower
description: An ominous tower with a fiery gaze that sees all... especially your enemies. It's not watching you, promise. Probably

name: Monster Tank Tower
description: A grotesque creature trapped in a tank. It’s angry, it’s ugly, and it’s ready to smash your enemies.

name: Tower of doom Mk I
description: A dark and menacing tower that channels unholy energy. It’s just getting started.

name: Tower of doom Mk II
description: The unholy energy grows stronger. This tower is ready to bring doom to your enemies.

name: Tower of doom Tower Mk III
description: The ultimate unholy weapon. This tower radiates pure doom and despair.

name: Tesla Tower Mk I
description: A crackling tower of electricity. It zaps enemies with shocking precision.

name: Tesla Tower Mk II
description: An advanced Tesla coil that unleashes devastating arcs of electricity.

name: Holy pillar
description: A radiant pillar that shines with pure energy. Enemies beware: this tower is blessed and a little bit smug about it.

name: Very Holy pillar
description: So holy it practically glows in the dark. This pillar doesn’t just smite evil—it does it with style.
